view. \r\n\r\nIt would be nice to give users the option to select and change their hotkeys. Especially for different/international keyboards, this can be very useful. At the moment, ASReview LAB supports the following hotkeys:\r\n\r\n```\r\nWhile reviewing, you can press a key (or a combination of keys) to label a record as relevant or irrelevant, to return to the previous decision, or to add a note.\r\n\r\nPress R or Shift + R:\r\n\r\nLabel a record as relevant\r\n\r\nPress I or Shift + I:\r\n\r\nLabel a record as irrelevant\r\n\r\nPress U or Shift + U:\r\n\r\nReturn to the previous decision\r\n\r\nPress N or Shift + N:\r\n\r\nAdd a note\r\n```\r\n\r\nMore hotkeys can also be added. \r\n\r\nðŸ’Ÿ  Added the help wanted tag to this feature request. We are welcoming contributions to this as we are not planning to work on this ourselves soon. ","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/asreview/asreview/issues/1076/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/asreview/asreview/issues/1076/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}